commit.message: Fix lint and broken and failing test.

Update ParamikoSSHClient.{put,putfo} method and make sure it correctly
handles absolute paths on Windows.
Fix lint.
Add tests for various new and existing ParamikoSSHClient methods.
Update changelog.
Add changelog entries.

Update exception which is thrown when reaching max tries to also include
the original traceback.
Also add method to the base class.

Add new keep_alive and use_compression argument to the ParamikoSSHClient
constructor.

Add new putfo() method to the ParamikoSSHClient and use that inside
FileDeployment step.

This method doesn't need to buffer whole file content in memory, can
utilize pipelining and it's much more efficient, especially for large
files.

For large files, it can be up to 70% faster compared to put().

Update put() method on the ParamikoSSHClient so we try to re-use the
underlying sftp connection if one already exists.

This results in performance improvements when uploading multiple files
over the same SSH client instance since it means we don't need to
re-open sftp connection for each new file upload or access.

Add a WIP change and update paramiko client to re-use existing sftp
connection.
Test enable compression and keep alive.
Add __str__ and __repr__ method to all the Deployment classes.
Update .gitignore.

Also try to close the connection before re-attempting to re-connect.

In most cases this won't be needed, but it's better we try to do that.

Add a test case which verifies _run_deployment_script() correctly tries
to reconnect in case "SSH session not active" exception is thrown.
Fix lint.
Fix lint.
Add changelog entry.

Try to reconnect if we receive "ssh connection not active" error during
deployment step run.

This may help in scenarios when connection is closed for some reason
before finishing running all the deployment steps.

ssh_client.close() throwing in reconnect retry loop should not be
closed - it could simply mean socket is already closed.
Add changelog entry.
Call new script from daily build cron job.
Make file executable.
Merge branch 'pricing-azure' of https://github.com/Eis-D-Z/libcloud into Eis-D-Z-pricing-azure
Also bump default value for wait_period argument in wait_until_running to 5 seconds.
Indicate we are working on a dev version.

Allow user to pass "wait_period" argument to the deploy_method() and
default it to a more reasonable value.
